The paper proposes a differentially private method for regression analysis, which involves optimization-based analyses. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.DB (Databases). Among these, cs.CR is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on privacy protection and proposes a new method for enforcing differential privacy. cs.LG is also a likely category, as the paper deals with regression analysis, which is a common task in machine learning. cs.DS and cs.IT are less likely categories, as they are more focused on theoretical aspects of computer science, while cs.DB is also a less likely category, as the paper does not primarily deal with database-related issues.
